msgctxt "dn28:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 28"
msgstr "Long Discourses 28"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn28:2.1"
msgid "Sampasādanīyasutta"
msgstr "Inspiring Confidence"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn28:3.1"
msgid "1. Sāriputtasīhanāda"
msgstr "Sāriputta’s Lion’s Roar"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.99"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:4.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn28:4.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā nāḷandāyaṃ viharati pāvārikambavane."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Nālandā in Pāvārika’s mango grove. "

msgctxt "dn28:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Sāriputta went up to the Buddha,"

msgctxt "dn28:4.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down to one side, "

msgctxt "dn28:4.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn28:4.6"
msgid ""
"“evaṃpasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati, na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi "
"vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ "
"sambodhiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I have such confidence in the Buddha that I believe there’s no other "
"ascetic or brahmin—whether past, future, or present—whose direct knowledge "
"is superior to the Buddha when it comes to awakening.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.100"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Uḷārā kho te ayaṃ, sāriputta, āsabhī vācā bhāsitā, ekaṃso gahito, sīhanādo "
"nadito:"
msgstr ""
"“That’s a grand and dramatic statement, Sāriputta. You’ve roared a "
"definitive, categorical lion’s roar, saying:"

msgctxt "dn28:5.2"
msgid "‘evaṃpasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati;"
msgstr "‘I have such confidence in the Buddha that"

msgctxt "dn28:5.3"
msgid ""
"na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā "
"bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ sambodhiyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"I believe there’s no other ascetic or brahmin—whether past, future, or "
"present—whose direct knowledge is superior to the Buddha when it comes to "
"awakening.’"

msgctxt "dn28:5.4"
msgid ""
"Kiṃ te, sāriputta, ye te ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, "
"sabbe te bhagavanto cetasā ceto paricca viditā:"
msgstr ""
"What about all the Perfected Ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who lived in "
"the past? Have you comprehended their minds to know that"

msgctxt "dn28:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃsīlā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃdhammā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, "
"evaṃpaññā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, evaṃvihārī te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipi, "
"evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto ahesuṃ itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"those Buddhas had such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or such "
"meditation, or such freedom?”"

msgctxt "dn28:5.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
#. VAR: pana te → kiṃ pana (pts1)
msgctxt "dn28:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana te, sāriputta, ye te bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto "
"sammāsambuddhā, sabbe te bhagavanto cetasā ceto paricca viditā:"
msgstr ""
"“And what about all the Perfected Ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who will "
"live in the future? Have you comprehended their minds to know that"

msgctxt "dn28:6.2"
msgid "‘evaṃsīlā te bhagavanto bhavissanti itipi, evaṃdhammā …"
msgstr ""
"those Buddhas will have such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or "
"such meditation, or such freedom?”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:6.3"
msgid "evaṃpaññā …"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:6.4"
msgid "evaṃvihārī …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:6.5"
msgid "evaṃvimuttā te bhagavanto bhavissanti itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:6.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
#. VAR: pana te → kiṃ pana (pts1)
msgctxt "dn28:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Kiṃ pana te, sāriputta, ahaṃ etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho cetasā ceto "
"paricca vidito:"
msgstr ""
"“And what about me, the Perfected One, the fully awakened Buddha at present? "
"Have you comprehended my mind to know that"

msgctxt "dn28:7.2"
msgid "‘evaṃsīlo bhagavā itipi, evaṃdhammo …"
msgstr ""
"I have such ethics, or such teachings, or such wisdom, or such meditation, "
"or such freedom?”"

msgctxt "dn28:7.3"
msgid "evaṃpañño …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:7.4"
msgid "evaṃvihārī …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:7.5"
msgid "evaṃvimutto bhagavā itipī’”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:7.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettha ca hi te, sāriputta, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu arahantesu "
"sammāsambuddhesu cetopariyañāṇaṃ natthi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, Sāriputta, given that you don’t comprehend the minds of Buddhas "
"past, future, or present,"

msgctxt "dn28:8.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kiṃ carahi te ayaṃ, sāriputta, uḷārā āsabhī vācā bhāsitā, ekaṃso "
"gahito, sīhanādo nadito:"
msgstr ""
"what exactly are you doing, making such an grand and dramatic statement, "
"roaring such a definitive, categorical lions roar?”"

msgctxt "dn28:8.3"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃpasanno ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavati, na cāhu na ca bhavissati na cetarahi "
"vijjati añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññataro yadidaṃ "
"sambodhiyan’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.101"></a>
#. VAR: Na kho me → na kho panetaṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn28:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Na kho me, bhante, atītānāgatapaccuppannesu arahantesu sammāsambuddhesu "
"cetopariyañāṇaṃ atthi."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, though I don’t comprehend the minds of Buddhas past, future, and "
"present, still I understand this by inference from the teaching."

#. VAR: Api ca me → kho me bhante (bj, pts1, mr)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:9.2"
msgid "Api ca me dhammanvayo vidito."
msgstr " "

#. VAR: daḷhuddhāpaṃ → daḷhuddāpaṃ (bj, pts1, mr) | daḷhaddhālaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn28:9.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, rañño paccantimaṃ nagaraṃ daḷhuddhāpaṃ "
"daḷhapākāratoraṇaṃ ekadvāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a king’s frontier citadel with fortified embankments, "
"ramparts, and arches, and a single gate."

msgctxt "dn28:9.4"
msgid ""
"Tatrassa dovāriko paṇḍito byatto medhāvī aññātānaṃ nivāretā, ñātānaṃ "
"pavesetā."
msgstr ""
"And it has a gatekeeper who is astute, competent, and clever. He keeps "
"strangers out and lets known people in."

msgctxt "dn28:9.5"
msgid ""
"So tassa nagarassa samantā anupariyāyapathaṃ anukkamamāno na passeyya "
"pākārasandhiṃ vā pākāravivaraṃ vā antamaso biḷāranikkhamanamattampi."
msgstr ""
"As he walks around the patrol path, he doesn’t see a hole or cleft in the "
"wall, not even one big enough for a cat to slip out."

msgctxt "dn28:9.6"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "dn28:9.7"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho keci oḷārikā pāṇā imaṃ nagaraṃ pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā, sabbe te "
"imināva dvārena pavisanti vā nikkhamanti vā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Whatever sizable creatures enter or leave the citadel, all of them do so "
"via this gate.’"

msgctxt "dn28:9.8"
msgid "Evameva kho me, bhante, dhammanvayo vidito."
msgstr "In the same way, I understand this by inference from the teaching:"

msgctxt "dn28:9.9"
msgid ""
"Ye te, bhante, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, sabbe te "
"bhagavanto pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
"catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā, satta sambojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ "
"bhāvetvā anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"‘All the perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas—whether past, future, or "
"present—give up the five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. Their mind is firmly established in the four kinds of mindfulness "
"meditation. They correctly develop the seven awakening factors. And they "
"wake up to the supreme perfect awakening.’”"

msgctxt "dn28:9.10"
msgid ""
"Yepi te, bhante, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, sabbe "
"te bhagavanto pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
"catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu suppatiṭṭhitacittā, satta sambojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ "
"bhāvetvā anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambujjhissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:9.11"
msgid ""
"Bhagavāpi, bhante, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya "
"cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe catūsu satipaṭṭhānesu "
"suppatiṭṭhitacitto satta sambojjhaṅge yathābhūtaṃ bhāvetvā anuttaraṃ "
"sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.102"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:10.1"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, bhante, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃ dhammassavanāya."
msgstr "Sir, once I approached the Buddha to listen to the teaching."

msgctxt "dn28:10.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti uttaruttaraṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ."
msgstr ""
"He explained Dhamma with its higher and higher stages, with its better and "
"better stages, with its dark and bright sides."

msgctxt "dn28:10.3"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā me, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ desesi uttaruttaraṃ paṇītapaṇītaṃ "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāgaṃ tathā tathāhaṃ tasmiṃ dhamme abhiññā idhekaccaṃ "
"dhammaṃ dhammesu niṭṭhamagamaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"When I directly knew a certain principle of those teachings, in accordance "
"with how I was taught, I came to a conclusion about the teachings. I had "
"confidence in the Teacher:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:10.4"
msgid "satthari pasīdiṃ:"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:10.5"
msgid ""
"‘sammāsambuddho bhagavā, svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, suppaṭipanno "
"sāvakasaṅgho’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The Blessed One is a fully awakened Buddha. The Dharma is well explained. "
"The Saṅgha is practicing well.’"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:11.1"
msgid "1.1. Kusaladhammadesanā"
msgstr "Teaching Skillful Qualities"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:12.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti kusalesu "
"dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches skillful qualities is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:12.2"
msgid "Tatrime kusalā dhammā seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "This consists of such skillful qualities as"

msgctxt "dn28:12.3"
msgid ""
"cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro iddhipādā, "
"pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo."
msgstr ""
"the four kinds of mindfulness meditation, the four right endeavors, the four "
"bases for psychic power, the five faculties, the five powers, the seven "
"factors of awakening, and the eightfold noble path."

msgctxt "dn28:12.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhante, bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"By these a mendicant realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And they live having achieved it with their own "
"insight due to the end of defilements."

msgctxt "dn28:12.5"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to skillful qualities."

msgctxt "dn28:12.6"
msgid ""
"Taṃ bhagavā asesamabhijānāti, taṃ bhagavato asesamabhijānato uttari "
"abhiññeyyaṃ natthi, yadabhijānaṃ añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā "
"bhiyyobhiññataro assa, yadidaṃ kusalesu dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha understands this without exception. There is nothing to be "
"understood beyond this whereby another ascetic or brahmin might be superior "
"in direct knowledge to the Buddha when it comes to skillful qualities."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:13.1"
msgid "1.2. Āyatanapaṇṇattidesanā"
msgstr "Describing the Sense Fields"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.103"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:14.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"āyatanapaṇṇattīsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the description of the sense "
"fields is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:14.2"
msgid "Chayimāni, bhante, ajjhattikabāhirāni āyatanāni."
msgstr "There are these six interior and exterior sense fields."

#. VAR: rūpā → rūpāni (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn28:14.3"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuñceva rūpā ca, sotañceva saddā ca, ghānañceva gandhā ca, jivhā ceva "
"rasā ca, kāyo ceva phoṭṭhabbā ca, mano ceva dhammā ca."
msgstr ""
"The eye and sights, the ear and sounds, the nose and smells, the tongue and "
"tastes, the body and touches, and the mind and thoughts."

msgctxt "dn28:14.4"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, āyatanapaṇṇattīsu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to describing the sense fields."

msgctxt "dn28:14.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ bhagavā asesamabhijānāti, taṃ bhagavato asesamabhijānato uttari "
"abhiññeyyaṃ natthi, yadabhijānaṃ añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā "
"bhiyyobhiññataro assa yadidaṃ āyatanapaṇṇattīsu."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha understands this without exception. There is nothing to be "
"understood beyond this whereby another ascetic or brahmin might be superior "
"in direct knowledge to the Buddha when it comes to describing the sense "
"fields."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:15.1"
msgid "1.3. Gabbhāvakkantidesanā"
msgstr "The Conception of the Embryo"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:16.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"gabbhāvakkantīsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the conception of the embryo is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:16.2"
msgid "Catasso imā, bhante, gabbhāvakkantiyo."
msgstr "There are these four kinds of conception."

msgctxt "dn28:16.3"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco asampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkamati;"
msgstr ""
"Firstly, someone is unaware when conceived in their mother’s womb, unaware "
"as they remain there, and unaware as they emerge. This is the first kind of "
"conception."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:16.4"
msgid "asampajāno mātukucchismiṃ ṭhāti;"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:16.5"
msgid "asampajāno mātukucchimhā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:16.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamā gabbhāvakkanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:17.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, idhekacco sampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkamati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, someone is aware when conceived in their mother’s womb, but "
"unaware as they remain there, and unaware as they emerge. This is the second "
"kind of conception."

msgctxt "dn28:17.2"
msgid "asampajāno mātukucchismiṃ ṭhāti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:17.3"
msgid "asampajāno mātukucchimhā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:17.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ dutiyā gabbhāvakkanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:18.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, idhekacco sampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkamati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, someone is aware when conceived in their mother’s womb, aware "
"as they remain there, but unaware as they emerge. This is the third kind of "
"conception."

msgctxt "dn28:18.2"
msgid "sampajāno mātukucchismiṃ ṭhāti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:18.3"
msgid "asampajāno mātukucchimhā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:18.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ tatiyā gabbhāvakkanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:19.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, idhekacco sampajāno mātukucchiṃ okkamati;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, someone is aware when conceived in their mother’s womb, aware "
"as they remain there, and aware as they emerge. This is the fourth kind of "
"conception."

msgctxt "dn28:19.2"
msgid "sampajāno mātukucchismiṃ ṭhāti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:19.3"
msgid "sampajāno mātukucchimhā nikkhamati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:19.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ catutthā gabbhāvakkanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:19.5"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, gabbhāvakkantīsu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to the conception of the embryo."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:20.1"
msgid "1.4. Ādesanavidhādesanā"
msgstr "Ways of Revealing"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:21.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"ādesanavidhāsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the different ways of revealing is "
"unsurpassable."

# Called ādesanāpāṭihāriya at AN 3.60
msgctxt "dn28:21.2"
msgid "Catasso imā, bhante, ādesanavidhā."
msgstr "There are these four ways of revealing."

msgctxt "dn28:21.3"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco nimittena ādisati:"
msgstr "Firstly, someone reveals by means of a sign:"

msgctxt "dn28:21.4"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state "
"of mind.’ "

msgctxt "dn28:21.5"
msgid "So bahuñcepi ādisati, tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"And even if they reveal this many times, it turns out exactly so, not "
"otherwise."

msgctxt "dn28:21.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamā ādesanavidhā."
msgstr "This is the first way of revealing."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:22.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhante, idhekacco na heva kho nimittena ādisati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, someone reveals after hearing it from a human or a non-human or "
"a god:  "

#, fuzzy
