#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:30.1"
msgid "1.6. Puggalapaṇṇattidesanā"
msgstr "Descriptions of Individuals"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wp" id="wp8"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:31.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"puggalapaṇṇattīsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the description of individuals is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:31.2"
msgid "Sattime, bhante, puggalā."
msgstr "There are these seven individuals."

msgctxt "dn28:31.3"
msgid ""
"Ubhatobhāgavimutto paññāvimutto kāyasakkhi diṭṭhippatto saddhāvimutto "
"dhammānusārī saddhānusārī."
msgstr ""
"One freed both ways, one freed by wisdom, a direct witness, one attained to "
"view, one freed by faith, a follower of principle, a follower by faith."

msgctxt "dn28:31.4"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, puggalapaṇṇattīsu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to the description of individuals."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:32.1"
msgid "1.7. Padhānadesanā"
msgstr "Kinds of Striving"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wp" id="wp9"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.106"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:33.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti padhānesu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the kinds of striving is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:33.2"
msgid ""
"Sattime, bhante, sambojjhaṅgā satisambojjhaṅgo dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgo "
"vīriyasambojjhaṅgo pītisambojjhaṅgo passaddhisambojjhaṅgo "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgo upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo."
msgstr ""
"There are these seven awakening factors: the awakening factors of "
"mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, "
"immersion, and equanimity. "

msgctxt "dn28:33.3"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, padhānesu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to the kinds of striving."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:34.1"
msgid "1.8. Paṭipadādesanā"
msgstr "Ways of Practice"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wp" id="wp10"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:35.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"paṭipadāsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the ways of practice is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:35.2"
msgid ""
"Catasso imā, bhante, paṭipadā dukkhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, dukkhā paṭipadā "
"khippābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā dandhābhiññā, sukhā paṭipadā khippābhiññāti."
msgstr ""
"~Painful practice with slow insight, ~painful practice with swift insight, ~"
"pleasant practice with slow insight, and ~pleasant practice with swift "
"insight."

msgctxt "dn28:35.3"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ, bhante, paṭipadā "
"ubhayeneva hīnā akkhāyati dukkhattā ca dandhattā ca."
msgstr ""
"Of these, the painful practice with slow insight is said to be inferior both "
"ways: because it’s painful and because it’s slow."

msgctxt "dn28:35.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ paṭipadā dukkhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ pana, bhante, "
"paṭipadā dukkhattā hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The painful practice with swift insight is said to be inferior because it’s "
"painful."

msgctxt "dn28:35.5"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā dandhābhiññā, ayaṃ pana, bhante, "
"paṭipadā dandhattā hīnā akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The pleasant practice with slow insight is said to be inferior because it’s "
"slow."

msgctxt "dn28:35.6"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhante, yāyaṃ paṭipadā sukhā khippābhiññā, ayaṃ pana, bhante, "
"paṭipadā ubhayeneva paṇītā akkhāyati sukhattā ca khippattā ca."
msgstr ""
"But the pleasant practice with swift insight is said to be superior both "
"ways: because it’s pleasant, and because it’s swift."

msgctxt "dn28:35.7"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, paṭipadāsu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to the ways of practice."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:36.1"
msgid "1.9. Bhassasamācārādidesanā"
msgstr "Behavior in Speech"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:37.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"bhassasamācāre."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches behavior in speech is "
"unsurpassable."

# Vehbutiya is only used here and DN 30, where the context shows it is a synonym for pesuniya.
msgctxt "dn28:37.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhante, ekacco na ceva musāvādupasañhitaṃ vācaṃ bhāsati na ca "
"vebhūtiyaṃ na ca pesuṇiyaṃ na ca sārambhajaṃ jayāpekkho;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone doesn’t use speech that’s connected with lying, nor "
"divisive, nor backbiting, nor aggressively trying to win."

msgctxt "dn28:37.3"
msgid "mantā mantā ca vācaṃ bhāsati nidhānavatiṃ kālena."
msgstr "They speak only wise counsel, valuable and timely."

msgctxt "dn28:37.4"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, bhassasamācāre."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to behavior in speech."

# For some reason Mahasangiti edition omits the heading here.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.107"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:38.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"purisasīlasamācāre."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches a person’s ethical behavior is "
"unsurpassable."

# Note that the sequence from satima to matima is related to the good qualities of Ananda, and pertain to textual fluency. Satima here is memory, not mindfulness, which is sato at the end.
#. VAR: nijigīsanako → nijihiṃsanako (bj) | nijigiṃsanako (s1-3) | nijigiṃsitā
#. (pts1)
msgctxt "dn28:38.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhante, ekacco sacco cassa saddho ca, na ca kuhako, na ca lapako, na "
"ca nemittiko, na ca nippesiko, na ca lābhena lābhaṃ nijigīsanako, indriyesu "
"guttadvāro, bhojane mattaññū, samakārī, jāgariyānuyogamanuyutto, atandito, "
"āraddhavīriyo, jhāyī, satimā, kalyāṇapaṭibhāno, gatimā, dhitimā, matimā, na "
"ca kāmesu giddho, sato ca nipako ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone is honest and faithful. They don’t use deception, "
"flattery, hinting, or belittling, and they don’t use material possessions to "
"pursue other material possessions. They guard the sense doors and eat in "
"moderation. They’re fair, committed to wakefulness, not slacking off, "
"energetic, and meditating. They have good memory, eloquence, range, "
"retention, and thoughtfulness. They’re not greedy for sensual pleasures. "
"They are mindful and self-disciplined."

msgctxt "dn28:38.3"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, purisasīlasamācāre."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to a person’s ethical behavior."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:39.1"
msgid "1.10. Anusāsanavidhādesanā"
msgstr "Responsiveness to Instruction"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:40.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"anusāsanavidhāsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the different degrees of "
"responsiveness to instruction is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:40.2"
msgid "Catasso imā, bhante, anusāsanavidhā—"
msgstr "There are these four degrees of responsiveness to instruction."

# paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā occurs at SN 46.8, MN 50, and DN 28. In MN 50 it clearly means "investigate inside himself". The same meaning makes sense in SN 46.8. In DN 28, it is applied to another.
msgctxt "dn28:40.3"
msgid ""
"jānāti, bhante, bhagavā aparaṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā ‘ayaṃ "
"puggalo yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā "
"sotāpanno bhavissati avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual: ‘By practicing "
"as instructed this individual will, with the ending of three fetters, become "
"a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for "
"awakening.’"

msgctxt "dn28:40.4"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:40.5"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ "
"parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī bhavissati, sakideva imaṃ "
"lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘By practicing as instructed this individual will, with the ending of three "
"fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and delusion, become a once-"
"returner. They will back to this world once only, then make an end of "
"suffering.’"

msgctxt "dn28:40.6"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:40.7"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ "
"saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko bhavissati tattha parinibbāyī "
"anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘By practicing as instructed this individual will, with the ending of the "
"five lower fetters, be reborn spontaneously. They will be extinguished "
"there, and are not liable to return from that world.’"

msgctxt "dn28:40.8"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:40.9"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ "
"cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘By practicing as instructed this individual will realize the undefiled "
"freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having "
"achieved it with their own insight due to the end of defilements.’"

msgctxt "dn28:40.10"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, anusāsanavidhāsu."
msgstr ""
"This is unsurpassable when it comes to the different degrees of "
"responsiveness to instruction."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:41.1"
msgid "1.11. Parapuggalavimuttiñāṇadesanā"
msgstr "The Knowledge and Freedom of Others"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.108"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:42.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"parapuggalavimuttiñāṇe."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the knowledge and freedom of other "
"individuals is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:42.2"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:42.3"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno bhavissati "
"avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘With the ending of three fetters this individual will become a stream-"
"enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.’"

msgctxt "dn28:42.4"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:42.5"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā "
"sakadāgāmī bhavissati, sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ "
"karissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘With the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and "
"delusion, this individual will become a once-returner. They will back to "
"this world once only, then make an end of suffering.’"

msgctxt "dn28:42.6"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:42.7"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko "
"bhavissati tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘With the ending of the five lower fetters, this individual will be reborn "
"spontaneously. They will be extinguished there, and are not liable to return "
"from that world.’"

msgctxt "dn28:42.8"
msgid "Jānāti, bhante, bhagavā paraṃ puggalaṃ paccattaṃ yonisomanasikārā:"
msgstr "The Buddha knows by investigating inside another individual:"

msgctxt "dn28:42.9"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ puggalo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva "
"dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This individual will realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life, and live having achieved it with their own insight "
"due to the end of defilements.’"

msgctxt "dn28:42.10"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, parapuggalavimuttiñāṇe."
msgstr ""
"This is unsurpassable when it comes to the knowledge and freedom of other "
"individuals."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:43.1"
msgid "1.12. Sassatavādadesanā"
msgstr "Eternalism"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.109"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:44.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"sassatavādesu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches eternalist doctrines is "
"unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:44.2"
msgid "Tayome, bhante, sassatavādā."
msgstr "There are these three eternalist doctrines."

msgctxt "dn28:44.3"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya …"
