#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:47.1"
msgid "1.13. Pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇadesanā"
msgstr "Recollecting Past Lives"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.111"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:48.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇe."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the knowledge of recollecting past "
"lives is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:48.2"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of "
"such a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "dn28:48.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:48.4"
msgid ""
"tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ "
"pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:48.5"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "That is:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:48.6"
msgid ""
"ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo "
"dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi "
"jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe "
"anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe, ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo "
"evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, "
"so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a "
"thousand, a hundred thousand lives; many eons of the world contracting, many "
"eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world contracting and evolving. "
"They remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like "
"this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that "
"was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn "
"somewhere else. "

msgctxt "dn28:48.7"
msgid ""
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti."
msgstr ""
"There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that "
"was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’"

msgctxt "dn28:48.8"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details. "

#. VAR: devā → sattā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn28:48.9"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhante, devā, yesaṃ na sakkā gaṇanāya vā saṅkhānena vā āyu saṅkhātuṃ."
msgstr "Sir, there are gods whose life span cannot be reckoned or calculated."

msgctxt "dn28:48.10"
msgid ""
"Api ca yasmiṃ yasmiṃ attabhāve abhinivuṭṭhapubbo hoti yadi vā rūpīsu yadi vā "
"arūpīsu yadi vā saññīsu yadi vā asaññīsu yadi vā nevasaññīnāsaññīsu."
msgstr ""
"Still, no matter what incarnation they have previously been reborn in—"
"whether physical or formless or percipient or non-percipient or neither "
"percipient nor non-percipient—"

msgctxt "dn28:48.11"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and details."

msgctxt "dn28:48.12"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇe."
msgstr ""
"This is unsurpassable when it comes to the knowledge of recollecting past "
"lives."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:49.1"
msgid "1.14. Cutūpapātañāṇadesanā"
msgstr "Death and Rebirth"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="wp" id="wp17"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.112"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:50.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti sattānaṃ "
"cutūpapātañāṇe."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches the knowledge of the death and "
"rebirth of sentient beings is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:50.2"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of "
"such a kind that with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see "
"sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, "
"beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how "
"sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:50.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:50.4"
msgid ""
"tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte dibbena cakkhunā "
"visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne "
"paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:50.5"
msgid ""
"‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena "
"samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā "
"micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā."
msgstr ""
"‘These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They "
"spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out "
"of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn "
"in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:50.6"
msgid ""
"Te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:50.7"
msgid ""
"Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena "
"samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā "
"sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā."
msgstr ""
"These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and "
"mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they "
"chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, "
"they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:50.8"
msgid "Te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:50.9"
msgid ""
"Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passati cavamāne "
"upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, they see sentient "
"beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and "
"ugly, in a good place or a bad place. They understand how sentient beings "
"are reborn according to their deeds."

msgctxt "dn28:50.10"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇe."
msgstr ""
"This is unsurpassable when it comes to the knowledge of death and rebirth."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:51.1"
msgid "1.15. Iddhividhadesanā"
msgstr "Psychic Powers"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="wp" id="wp18"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:52.1"
msgid ""
"Aparaṃ pana, bhante, etadānuttariyaṃ, yathā bhagavā dhammaṃ deseti "
"iddhividhāsu."
msgstr ""
"And moreover, sir, how the Buddha teaches psychic powers is unsurpassable."

msgctxt "dn28:52.2"
msgid "Dvemā, bhante, iddhividhāyo—"
msgstr "There are these two kinds of psychic power:"

msgctxt "dn28:52.3"
msgid "atthi, bhante, iddhi sāsavā saupadhikā, ‘no ariyā’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"There are psychic powers that are accompanied by defilements and "
"attachments, and are said to be ignoble."

msgctxt "dn28:52.4"
msgid "Atthi, bhante, iddhi anāsavā anupadhikā ‘ariyā’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"There are psychic powers that are free of defilements and attachments, and "
"are said to be noble."

msgctxt "dn28:52.5"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhante, iddhi sāsavā saupadhikā, ‘no ariyā’ti vuccati?"
msgstr ""
"What are the psychic powers that are accompanied by defilements and "
"attachments, and are said to be ignoble?"

msgctxt "dn28:52.6"
msgid "Idha, bhante, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences an immersion of the heart of "
"such a kind that they wield the many kinds of psychic power:"

msgctxt "dn28:52.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:52.8"
msgid ""
"tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ "
"iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:52.9"
msgid "ekopi hutvā bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti;"
msgstr "multiplying themselves and becoming one again; "

msgctxt "dn28:52.10"
msgid ""
"āvibhāvaṃ tirobhāvaṃ tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati "
"seyyathāpi ākāse;"
msgstr ""
"going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space;"
" "

msgctxt "dn28:52.11"
msgid "pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti seyyathāpi udake;"
msgstr "diving in and out of the earth as if it was water; "

msgctxt "dn28:52.12"
msgid "udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ;"
msgstr "walking on water as if it was earth; "

msgctxt "dn28:52.13"
msgid "ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo;"
msgstr "flying cross-legged through the air like a bird;"

msgctxt "dn28:52.14"
msgid ""
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parāmasati "
"parimajjati;"
msgstr ""
"touching and stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful;"

msgctxt "dn28:52.15"
msgid "yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti."
msgstr "controlling the body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

msgctxt "dn28:52.16"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhante, iddhi sāsavā saupadhikā, ‘no ariyā’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"These are the psychic powers that are accompanied by defilements and "
"attachments, and are said to be ignoble."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.113"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:53.1"
msgid "Katamā pana, bhante, iddhi anāsavā anupadhikā, ‘ariyā’ti vuccati?"
msgstr ""
"But what are the psychic powers that are free of defilements and "
"attachments, and are said to be noble?"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:53.2"
msgid "Idha, bhante, bhikkhu sace ākaṅkhati:"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn28:53.3"
msgid ""
"‘paṭikūle appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, if a mendicant wishes: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive "
"in the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "dn28:53.4"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:53.5"
msgid "‘appaṭikūle paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha viharati."
msgstr ""
"If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive,’ "
"that’s what they do."

msgctxt "dn28:53.6"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:53.7"
msgid ""
"‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca appaṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, appaṭikūlasaññī "
"tattha viharati."
msgstr ""
"If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the unrepulsive in the repulsive "
"and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "dn28:53.8"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:53.9"
msgid ""
"‘paṭikūle ca appaṭikūle ca paṭikūlasaññī vihareyyan’ti, paṭikūlasaññī tattha "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"If they wish: ‘May I meditate perceiving the repulsive in the unrepulsive "
"and the repulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "dn28:53.10"
msgid "Sace ākaṅkhati:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:53.11"
msgid ""
"‘paṭikūlañca appaṭikūlañca tadubhayaṃ abhinivajjetvā upekkhako vihareyyaṃ "
"sato sampajāno’ti, upekkhako tattha viharati sato sampajāno."
msgstr ""
"If they wish: ‘May I meditate staying equanimous, mindful and aware, "
"rejecting both the repulsive and the unrepulsive,’ that’s what they do. "

msgctxt "dn28:53.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhante, iddhi anāsavā anupadhikā ‘ariyā’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"These are the psychic powers that are free of defilements and attachments, "
"and are said to be noble."

msgctxt "dn28:53.13"
msgid "Etadānuttariyaṃ, bhante, iddhividhāsu."
msgstr "This is unsurpassable when it comes to psychic powers."

msgctxt "dn28:53.14"
msgid ""
"Taṃ bhagavā asesamabhijānāti, taṃ bhagavato asesamabhijānato uttari "
"abhiññeyyaṃ natthi, yadabhijānaṃ añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā "
"bhiyyobhiññataro assa yadidaṃ iddhividhāsu."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha understands this without exception. There is nothing to be "
"understood beyond this whereby another ascetic or brahmin might be superior "
"in direct knowledge to the Buddha when it comes to psychic powers."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:54.1"
msgid "1.16. Aññathāsatthuguṇadassana"
msgstr "The Four Absorptions"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="wp" id="wp19"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:55.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ taṃ, bhante, saddhena kulaputtena pattabbaṃ āraddhavīriyena thāmavatā "
"purisathāmena purisavīriyena purisaparakkamena purisadhorayhena, anuppattaṃ "
"taṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha has achieved what should be achieved by a faithful person of "
"respectable family by being energetic and strong, by manly strength, energy, "
"vigor, and exertion."

msgctxt "dn28:55.2"
msgid ""
"Na ca, bhante, bhagavā kāmesu kāmasukhallikānuyogamanuyutto hīnaṃ gammaṃ "
"pothujjanikaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ, na ca attakilamathānuyogamanuyutto "
"dukkhaṃ anariyaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The Buddha doesn’t indulge in sensual pleasures, which are low, crass, "
"ordinary, ignoble, and pointless. And he doesn’t indulge in self-"
"mortification, which is painful, ignoble, and pointless."

msgctxt "dn28:55.3"
msgid ""
"Catunnañca bhagavā jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ "
"nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī."
msgstr ""
"He gets the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when he wants, without trouble or difficulty."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn28:56.1"
msgid "1.17. Anuyogadānappakāra"
msgstr "On Being Questioned"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.114"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:57.1"
msgid "Sace maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyya:"
msgstr "Sir, if they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "dn28:57.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ aññe samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā "
"vā bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññatarā sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, ‘no’"
"ti vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Sāriputta, is there any other ascetic or brahmin—whether past, "
"future, or present—whose direct knowledge is superior to the Buddha when it "
"comes to awakening?’ I would tell them ‘No.’"

msgctxt "dn28:57.3"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ aññe samaṇā vā "
"brāhmaṇā vā bhagavatā bhiyyobhiññatarā sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, "
"bhante, ‘no’ti vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:57.4"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, atthetarahi añño samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā bhagavatā "
"bhiyyobhiññataro sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, ‘no’ti vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:58.1"
msgid "Sace pana maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyya:"
msgstr "But if they were to ask me:"

msgctxt "dn28:58.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ aññe samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā "
"vā bhagavatā samasamā sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, ‘evan’ti "
"vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverend Sāriputta, is there any other ascetic or brahmin—whether past or "
"future—whose direct knowledge is equal to the Buddha when it comes to "
"awakening?’ I would tell them ‘Yes.’"

msgctxt "dn28:58.3"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ aññe samaṇā vā "
"brāhmaṇā vā bhagavatā samasamā sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, "
"‘evan’ti vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:58.4"
msgid ""
"‘Kiṃ panāvuso sāriputta, atthetarahi aññe samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā bhagavatā "
"samasamā sambodhiyan’ti, evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, ‘no’ti vadeyyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But if they were to ask: ‘Reverend Sāriputta, is there any other ascetic or "
"brahmin at present whose direct knowledge is equal to the Buddha when it "
"comes to awakening?’ I would tell them ‘No.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:59.1"
msgid "Sace pana maṃ, bhante, evaṃ puccheyya:"
msgstr "But if they were to ask me:"

# here the abhi- in abbhanujanati doesn't have an elevated sense, but the "meta-" sense: you grant this regarding one but not the other.
msgctxt "dn28:59.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃ panāyasmā sāriputto ekaccaṃ abbhanujānāti, ekaccaṃ na abbhanujānātī’ti, "
"evaṃ puṭṭho ahaṃ, bhante, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"‘But why does Venerable Sāriputta grant this in respect of some but not "
"others?’ I would answer them like this:"

#. VAR: paṭiggahitaṃ → ^mn115#14 [Bahu­dhātu­ka­sutta]; ^an1.268-277#277.1
#. [268/277]; ^ne4#414 [Vibhaṅga/ Vicaya­hā­rasam­pāta]; ^mi6.1.1#1
#. [Dvin­naṃ­buddhā­na­ṃa­nup­paj­ja­māna­pañha] ^vb16#353 [Mātikā/
#. Dasakaniddesa]
msgctxt "dn28:59.3"
msgid "‘sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "‘Reverends, I have heard and learned this directly from the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn28:59.4"
msgid ""
"“ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā mayā samasamā sambodhiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“The perfected ones, fully awakened Buddhas of the past and the future are "
"equal to myself when it comes to awakening.”"

msgctxt "dn28:59.5"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ, sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:59.6"
msgid ""
"“bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā mayā samasamā "
"sambodhiyan”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn28:59.7"
msgid "Sammukhā metaṃ, āvuso, bhagavato sutaṃ sammukhā paṭiggahitaṃ:"
msgstr "And I have also heard and learned this directly from the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn28:59.8"
msgid ""
"“aṭṭhānametaṃ anavakāso yaṃ ekissā lokadhātuyā dve arahanto sammāsambuddhā "
"apubbaṃ acarimaṃ uppajjeyyuṃ, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”’ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s impossible that two Perfect Ones, fully awakened Buddhas, could arise "
"in the same solar system at the same time.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.115"></a>
#. VAR: vādānuvādo → vādānupāto (bj)
msgctxt "dn28:60.1"
msgid ""
"Kaccāhaṃ, bhante, evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva bhagavato "
"homi, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhāmi, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ "
"byākaromi, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Answering this way, I trust that I repeated what the Buddha has said, and "
"didn’t misrepresent him with an untruth. I trust my explanation was in line "
"with the teaching, and that there are no legitimate grounds for rebuke or "
"criticism.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:61.1"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tvaṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ puṭṭho evaṃ byākaramāno vuttavādī ceva me "
"hosi, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhasi, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākarosi, na "
"ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, Sāriputta, in answering this way you repeat what I’ve said, and don’"
"t misrepresent me with an untruth. Your explanation is in line with the "
"teaching, and there are no legitimate grounds for rebuke or criticism.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn28:62.1"
msgid "2. Acchariyaabbhuta"
msgstr "Incredible and Amazing"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="wp" id="wp20"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:63.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he had spoken, Venerable Udāyī said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn28:63.2"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, tathāgatassa appicchatā santuṭṭhitā "
"sallekhatā."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! The Realized One has so few wishes, "
"such contentment, such self-effacement!"

msgctxt "dn28:63.3"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma tathāgato evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo, atha ca pana "
"nevattānaṃ pātukarissati."
msgstr ""
"For even though the Realized One has such power and might, he will not make "
"a display of himself."

msgctxt "dn28:63.4"
msgid ""
"Ekamekañcepi ito, bhante, dhammaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā attani "
"samanupasseyyuṃ, te tāvatakeneva paṭākaṃ parihareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the wanderers following other paths were to see even a single one of "
"these qualities in themselves they’d carry around a banner to that effect."

msgctxt "dn28:63.5"
msgid ""
"Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante, tathāgatassa appicchatā santuṭṭhitā "
"sallekhatā."
msgstr ""
"It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! The Realized One has so few wishes, such "
"contentment, such self-effacement!"

msgctxt "dn28:63.6"
msgid "Yatra hi nāma tathāgato evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo."
msgstr ""
"For even though the Realized One has such power and might, he will not make "
"a display of himself.”"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn28:63.7"
msgid "Atha ca pana nevattānaṃ pātukarissatī”ti."
msgstr " "

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:64.1"
msgid ""
"“Passa kho tvaṃ, udāyi, ‘tathāgatassa appicchatā santuṭṭhitā sallekhatā."
msgstr ""
"“See, Udāyī, how the Realized One has so few wishes, such contentment, such "
"self-effacement."

msgctxt "dn28:64.2"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma tathāgato evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo, atha ca pana "
"nevattānaṃ pātukarissati’."
msgstr ""
"For even though the Realized One has such power and might, he will not make "
"a display of himself."

msgctxt "dn28:64.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamekañcepi ito, udāyi, dhammaṃ aññatitthiyā paribbājakā attani "
"samanupasseyyuṃ, te tāvatakeneva paṭākaṃ parihareyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the wanderers following other paths were to see even a single one of "
"these qualities in themselves they’d carry around a banner to that effect."

msgctxt "dn28:64.4"
msgid "Passa kho tvaṃ, udāyi, ‘tathāgatassa appicchatā santuṭṭhitā sallekhatā."
msgstr ""
"See, Udāyī, how the Realized One has so few wishes, such contentment, such "
"self-effacement."

msgctxt "dn28:64.5"
msgid ""
"Yatra hi nāma tathāgato evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo, atha ca pana "
"nevattānaṃ pātukarissatī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"For even though the Realized One has such power and might, he will not make "
"a display of himself.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="wp" id="wp21"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.116"></a>
msgctxt "dn28:65.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Venerable Sāriputta:"

msgctxt "dn28:65.2"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha tvaṃ, sāriputta, imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ bhāseyyāsi "
"bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ upāsakānaṃ upāsikānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So Sāriputta, you should frequently speak this explanation of the teaching "
"to the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen."

msgctxt "dn28:65.3"
msgid ""
"Yesampi hi, sāriputta, moghapurisānaṃ bhavissati tathāgate kaṅkhā vā vimati "
"vā, tesamimaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ sutvā tathāgate kaṅkhā vā vimati vā, sā "
"pahīyissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Though there will be some foolish people who have doubt or uncertainty "
"regarding the Realized One, when they hear this explanation of the teaching "
"they’ll give up that doubt or uncertainty.”"

msgctxt "dn28:65.4"
msgid "Iti hidaṃ āyasmā sāriputto bhagavato sammukhā sampasādaṃ pavedesi."
msgstr ""
"That’s how Venerable Sāriputta declared his confidence in the Buddha’s "
"presence."

msgctxt "dn28:65.5"
msgid "Tasmā imassa veyyākaraṇassa sampasādanīyantveva adhivacananti."
msgstr "And that’s why the name of this discussion is “Inspiring Confidence”."

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn28:66.1"
msgid "Sampasādanīyasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
